1
00:00:21,062 --> 00:00:22,230
Leave them here.

2
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:28,945
-That should go in the back seat.
-Yes, sir.

3
00:00:30,613 --> 00:00:33,992
If you bribe someone like this,
you'll be caught right away.

4
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:38,204
I guess you could call this a bribe.

5
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:41,207
Today is your future
father-in-law's birthday.

6
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:42,500
What?

7
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:46,504
I'm grateful enough that
you came to wish me a happy birthday.

8
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:48,506
You really didn't have to bring anything.

9
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:52,010
Su-ryeon, get over here.

10
00:00:52,093 --> 00:00:54,429
Mr. Hwang sent us this precious gift.

11
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:57,724
A gift? What gift?

12
00:00:57,807 --> 00:01:00,727
And his son brought it
all the way here in person.

13
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:15,158
We must expel

14
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:18,119
all government-funded professors,
who have lived as parasites

15
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:21,081
of the Yushin dictatorship
from our sacred campus!

16
00:01:40,850 --> 00:01:43,186
You must be surprised
that I showed up unannounced,

17
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:44,771
Su-ryeon.

18
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,541
Why are you standing around?
Come have a seat.

19
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,295
Guys, come have a seat.

20
00:02:09,379 --> 00:02:11,881
Well, I should get going.

21
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:15,760
Why? Stay and eat with us.

22
00:02:17,011 --> 00:02:19,097
No, you have a guest.

23
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:22,642
Are you uncomfortable?

24
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:25,311
No, I'm fine.

25
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:29,566
But Su-ryeon's friend can do
as she wishes.

26
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,236
I'll get going, then.

27
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:34,821
Myeong-hee!

28
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:38,241
Where are you going? Stay and eat with us.

29
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:40,827
-No, I should get going.
-Come on.

30
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:43,121
I bought a cake.

31
00:02:43,204 --> 00:02:45,582
Just stay and eat with us.

32
00:02:47,917 --> 00:02:48,918
Who might this be?

33
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:51,379
Su-chan.

34
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:55,008
This is Mr. Hwang's son.
I told you about him the other day.

35
00:02:55,675 --> 00:02:57,927
The guy Su-ryeon has been seeing?

36
00:03:02,473 --> 00:03:04,017
I'm Hwang Hui-tae.

37
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:07,353
Nice to meet you.

38
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:10,189
I'm Lee Su-chan, Su-ryeon's brother.

39
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:27,832
-Happy birthday!
-Happy birthday.

40
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:29,292
-Eat up.
-Thank you.

41
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:32,045
Let's eat. Eat up.

42
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:41,387
Goodness.

43
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:44,349
I'm sorry that all we did was put
an extra spoon on the table.

44
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:47,310
I would've gotten a hen
if you told us you were coming.

45
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:49,395
A hen? Please, Dad.

46
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:52,732
If you cooked a hen on top of this,
the table would collapse.

47
00:03:52,815 --> 00:03:54,984
It's a humble spread,
but eat as much as you want.

48
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:56,319
-Please.
-Will do.

49
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:57,737
By the way, Hui-tae.

50
00:03:58,404 --> 00:04:01,157
Su-ryeon is such a tomboy.
What do you like about her?

51
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:04,410
Don't say that you like everything
about her. That's such a cliche.

52
00:04:04,494 --> 00:04:05,703
Why do you like her?

53
00:04:06,996 --> 00:04:08,498
Well…

54
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:12,460
This place isn't open to just anyone.

55
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:14,504
Can we trust you?

56
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:21,177
She left a strong first impression on me.

57
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:28,268
Right away, she said we should go print
some anti-government flyers.

58
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:38,903
My gosh, you're really something.

59
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,029
Jeez.

60
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:44,701
Su-ryeon, what about you?
What do you like about him?

61
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:46,494
Are you losing your mind?

62
00:04:46,577 --> 00:04:48,162
Why must you ask such a question?

63
00:04:48,246 --> 00:04:49,956
I'm curious too.

64
00:04:50,039 --> 00:04:52,959
I want to know
how you've felt about me until now.

65
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,217
The thing is…

66
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:12,937
Whatever, never mind. Let's just eat.

67
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:17,483
My gosh. It seems like
you really should get married soon.

68
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:20,111
I've never seen you get so shy.

69
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:23,364
I told you! It's really not like that.

70
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:26,659
Goodness, you and your temper.

71
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:33,708
You know them well, don't you?

72
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:35,001
What?

73
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:39,922
I meant the rice cake place
that you go often.

74
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:43,384
I should order some rice cakes
for the grand opening.

75
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,762
Will they take good care of me
if I go alone?

76
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:49,348
Why don't I go there
and place the order for you?

77
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:50,892
It's very close to my house, you know.

78
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:52,769
Let's just go together then.

79
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:56,064
How about we meet there
before your shift tomorrow?

80
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:00,443
All right, then. Come on.

81
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:07,283
Dad, shall I tell them
to come back inside?

82
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:10,203
No, leave them alone. Don't ruin the mood.

83
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:29,388
I'll drop the honorifics
since we're the same age.

84
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,808
What kind of scheme brings you here?

85
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:33,017
Me?

86
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:35,394
I'm here to figure out your scheme.

87
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:39,148
What was your purpose
behind starting this ruse?

88
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,818
And what do you plan to do going forward?

89
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:51,327
My purpose and plan? It's simple.

90
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:54,997
I don't want to marry you.
Go ahead and reject me.

91
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:57,792
You need to gauge the situation better.

92
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:00,670
I'm the one who has leverage over you.

93
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:03,548
Reject you? Why would I?
It'll be such a hassle.

94
00:07:03,631 --> 00:07:06,259
All I need to do is tell our parents
what you did.

95
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:08,010
Go ahead then!

96
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:10,471
Why bother playing along?

97
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:13,933
I don't want to get Myeong-hee
into trouble.

98
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:17,395
Why are you bringing her up
all of a sudden?

99
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:19,730
She has nothing to do with you.

100
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,445
I like her, that's why.

101
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:26,446
What?

102
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:28,531
Who?

103
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,576
You like Myeong-hee?

104
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:33,744
Yes, I like Myeong-hee.
Got a problem with that?

105
00:07:34,328 --> 00:07:39,167
Hey, I sent Myeong-hee there
to be rejected in my place.

106
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:44,380
Right. If getting rejected was your goal,
you should've come yourself.

107
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:47,884
Why did you have to send Myeong-hee
as your stand-in and complicate things?

108
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:50,344
You're being ridiculous.

109
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:52,805
I think you got the wrong idea.

110
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:55,141
Don't you dare hit on her.

111
00:07:55,808 --> 00:07:58,978
Myeong-hee has no feelings for you
whatsoever.

112
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:00,563
In fact, she can't stand you.

113
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:01,689
Well…

114
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,775
I have a hard time believing you.

115
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:08,696
You don't seem all that interested
in other people's feelings.

116
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,617
Money is the reason she's been seeing you.

117
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:15,119
What?

118
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:18,915
Myeong-hee has been forcing herself
to see you to earn money.

119
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:25,338
Why?

120
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:28,966
Did you actually think
that she had feelings for you?

121
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:32,053
Yes.

122
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,642
What's with her suddenly?

123
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,645
Did you two
have a lover's quarrel or what?

124
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:45,608
Thank you so much for today.

125
00:08:45,691 --> 00:08:48,027
And happy birthday, sir.

126
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,111
Thanks.

127
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:51,906
Gosh, I almost forgot.

128
00:08:51,989 --> 00:08:54,033
I almost sent you home empty-handed.

129
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:55,034
Right.

130
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:57,203
We packed some food for you.
Wait right here.

131
00:08:57,286 --> 00:08:58,538
It's okay.

132
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,134
Is your leg okay?

133
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:20,685
It's true that I missed you,
but I didn't expect to see you here.

134
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,648
Hui-tae.

135
00:09:56,721 --> 00:10:00,349
Then I'll see you again next time,
Myeong-hee.

136
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:03,769
Hui-tae, here.

137
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:05,896
Gosh, there was no need.

138
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:09,358
It's nothing much,
so no need to feel uncomfortable.

139
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,735
Okay, thank you.

140
00:10:10,818 --> 00:10:12,945
-Drop by again next time.
-Sure.

141
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:20,953
Anyway, I'm afraid we'll have to maintain
this situation for the time being.

142
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:24,206
What? Do you mean you'll keep lying?

143
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:27,335
What do you mean? It's not a lie.

144
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:28,919
What I mean is,

145
00:10:29,003 --> 00:10:32,173
we'll just continue not to tell the truth
for a while.

146
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:37,261
Whenever I tell my dad
I'm going to meet him,

147
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:39,972
he's totally okay with it
whether it's day or night.

148
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:41,641
If he's going to find out anyway,

149
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:45,478
why don't we get what we need out of it
and worry about the aftermath later?

150
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:48,147
My goodness, you're totally crazy!

151
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:51,108
What if things get out of hand?
What will you do then?

152
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:53,569
Gosh, I don't know.

153
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:57,156
Anyway, let's stop talking about that.

154
00:10:57,948 --> 00:10:58,949
The thing is…

155
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:02,787
Myeong-hee, can I ask you something?

156
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:03,871
What?

157
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:06,082
Well…

158
00:11:07,124 --> 00:11:08,668
Do you

159
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:12,088
like Hwang Hui-tae?

160
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:19,970
What are you talking about?

161
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:21,931
No way!

162
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:23,599
Right?

163
00:11:23,682 --> 00:11:25,351
Okay, I'm glad to hear that.

164
00:11:25,893 --> 00:11:29,939
I made it quite certain
that he won't hit on you anymore.

165
00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:32,650
What did you say to him?

166
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:34,318
I told him you're meeting him
to make money

167
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:36,529
and you have
no feelings for him whatsoever.

168
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:39,532
Did you really say that?

169
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:40,616
Yes. Why?

170
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:43,285
It's the truth, isn't it?
You won't see him again anyway.

171
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:47,957
Are you seeing him again?

172
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:53,921
No.

173
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:01,137
TONIGHT AT 7 P.M.,
MUSIC CAFE HEE HEE NAK RAK

174
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:10,187
What is it?

175
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:12,857
Is something wrong?

176
00:12:13,649 --> 00:12:15,693
You look like an antsy dog.

177
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:20,781
The thing is…

178
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:24,994
A friend of mine wants to see me.

179
00:12:25,744 --> 00:12:27,872
But my best friend

180
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:29,999
hates that friend so much.

181
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:32,960
And she said
she won't hang out with us anymore.

182
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:34,712
Then don't meet that friend.

183
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:39,717
What if that friend keeps waiting,
thinking I'll show up?

184
00:12:41,677 --> 00:12:43,762
Then meet secretly.

185
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:46,474
Then I'll be lying to my best friend.

186
00:12:47,057 --> 00:12:49,018
Don't meet the first friend then.

187
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,896
-But…
-Man, whatever.

188
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:54,690
If you want to go, just go.
If you don't, don't.

189
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:56,525
What's gotten into you?

190
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:14,960
The DJ at this place is kind of ugly,

191
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:18,297
but he plays some amazing songs…

192
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:20,341
Hey, two o'clock, look.

193
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:21,425
Two o'clock?

194
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:32,978
He's gorgeous, isn't he?

195
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:40,152
-Hey, give me some lipstick.
-Lipstick?

196
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:42,112
What for?

197
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:44,657
Are you going to go talk to him?

198
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,242
Are you insane?

199
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:48,953
Only a woman with courage
gets the hot guy.

200
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:51,413
I'll go fix my makeup and go right over.

201
00:13:57,878 --> 00:13:58,963
Myeong-hee.

202
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:11,892
It'll taste bad
if you keep stirring it like that.

203
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,270
That's how I like it.

204
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:27,366
Why did you ask to meet me?

205
00:14:31,495 --> 00:14:33,789
I promised to play my song for you.

206
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:38,252
Were you waiting for me
all this time for that?

207
00:14:39,753 --> 00:14:42,631
What about you then? Why did you come?

208
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:46,677
I came to apologize.

209
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:50,139
I'm sorry for deceiving you all this time.

210
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:56,145
Why are you apologizing?
You never deceived me.

211
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:59,273
Why didn't you say anything when you knew?

212
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:03,402
If I said something,
we wouldn't be able to meet.

213
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:09,533
I wanted to keep seeing you,
and I still do.

214
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:14,038
You want to keep meeting me?

215
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:16,498
Yes, I do.

216
00:15:17,499 --> 00:15:20,878
I'm not the person you think I am.

217
00:15:20,961 --> 00:15:22,504
I'm not the daughter
of Changhwa Industrial either.

218
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:24,632
I know. The cheeky nurse
from the ER, right?

219
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:31,305
I'm the eldest daughter
of a penniless family,

220
00:15:31,388 --> 00:15:33,933
and I dropped out of high school
and took the GED.

221
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:38,437
I was born out of wedlock.

222
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,856
My mom used to sing at nightclubs.

223
00:15:46,862 --> 00:15:49,198
But what's the problem with that?

224
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:54,328
Thanks to our pasts, we turned out to be
strong and interesting people.

225
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:04,046
The truth is,

226
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:06,215
next month, I'm…

227
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:19,979
Hey!

228
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:29,071
Wait, lady.

229
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:35,619
That blouse looks very familiar.

230
00:16:38,747 --> 00:16:42,084
Right, I know that face too.

231
00:16:42,751 --> 00:16:46,088
But that person should be
studying in the library right now.

232
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:50,300
Myeong-hee, please don't tell Dad
about this.

233
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:10,863
Gosh.

234
00:17:12,281 --> 00:17:15,701
Do you know Myeong-hee?

235
00:17:17,911 --> 00:17:18,954
Yes.

236
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:35,554
It's my first time actually seeing
someone who goes to SNU.

237
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,348
May I hold your hand?

238
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:40,517
What are you doing?

239
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:41,810
Behave yourself.

240
00:17:46,231 --> 00:17:48,650
Myeong-hee,
what's your relationship with Jin-a?

241
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:49,902
We live together.

242
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:53,238
-My dad owns some real estate.
-It's just a boarding house.

243
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:56,033
I see. A boarding house.

244
00:18:02,539 --> 00:18:04,124
Jin-a, do you have a pen?

245
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:07,294
Shall I give you my pencil case?

246
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:09,838
If it's okay with you,
can you write down your number?

247
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:18,263
I'll write it with a permanent marker.

248
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:22,309
-What are you doing?
-What?

249
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:25,813
I just want to talk about music
with her someday

250
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:27,689
since we're both music fanatics.

251
00:18:29,274 --> 00:18:30,651
By the way,

252
00:18:30,734 --> 00:18:34,780
how do you and Myeong-hee know each other?

253
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:36,323
Well…

254
00:18:37,449 --> 00:18:39,618
-Myeong-hee and I--
-Our bus is here.

255
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,411
Get up.

256
00:19:04,768 --> 00:19:05,894
Hello?

257
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:08,355
It's you, Hui-tae.

258
00:19:09,606 --> 00:19:12,818
Su-ryeon? You haven't met her?

259
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:15,320
I see.

260
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:18,699
So she said she had a date with me.

261
00:19:21,285 --> 00:19:24,079
No. We do have a date.

262
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:26,081
All right. Have a great time.

263
00:19:35,591 --> 00:19:38,010
Su-chan. Are you going somewhere?

264
00:19:38,093 --> 00:19:40,262
I'm going to order rice cakes
for the opening ceremony.

265
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:42,514
I'm running late. I'll see you later.

266
00:19:45,809 --> 00:19:48,896
-Have you been well?
-Hey, it's been a while.

267
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,189
Hold on.

268
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:51,440
Are you here to order rice cakes
for your wedding?

269
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:55,694
Our wedding? It's not like that.

270
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:58,530
What are you talking about?
It's for his opening ceremony.

271
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:00,824
Can you prepare them by tomorrow morning?

272
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:03,493
Tomorrow morning?
We're a bit backlogged here.

273
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:05,370
I don't think we can.

274
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:06,914
Come on.

275
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:10,000
You should never miss a customer
who's having an opening ceremony.

276
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:12,794
I brought him here
so he'd become your regular.

277
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:15,214
Have them ready by tomorrow morning, okay?

278
00:20:16,381 --> 00:20:17,716
What are you going to order, anyway?

279
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:21,553
-First, some red-bean rice cakes.
-Red-bean rice cakes.

280
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:22,554
Hold on.

281
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:25,474
These red beans look a bit old.

282
00:20:25,557 --> 00:20:29,686
-Do you have any newer batches?
-Jeez, they were delivered this morning.

283
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:32,564
Also, rice cakes made with old beans
taste better.

284
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:33,982
Don't use these.

285
00:20:34,691 --> 00:20:37,486
Use the ones that you hid in the back.

286
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:39,112
They're all the same.

287
00:20:39,196 --> 00:20:41,573
-Can we get a discount?
-Of course.

288
00:20:42,157 --> 00:20:44,326
Su-chan, do you want to
have them delivered?

289
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:48,997
What? Yes, that sounds good.

290
00:20:54,127 --> 00:20:56,338
If I'd come here alone,
my guests would've had

291
00:20:56,421 --> 00:20:58,548
just one bite of rice cake each.

292
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:02,010
It's better to have too much.
It's a celebration.

293
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:04,763
Hold on. Shouldn't you eat before work?

294
00:21:04,846 --> 00:21:07,766
-What do you want to eat?
-Don't worry. I'll eat at the hospital.

295
00:21:07,849 --> 00:21:11,186
Come on. Let me buy you something nice.

296
00:21:12,312 --> 00:21:14,690
Are there any good places around here?

297
00:21:18,026 --> 00:21:20,737
WATCH REPAIR

298
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:32,708
You don't want ribs, do you?

299
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:39,464
-Let's go eat somewhere else.
-Should we do that?

300
00:21:47,556 --> 00:21:50,350
What? Marriage?

301
00:21:51,810 --> 00:21:54,271
It seems like the parents
are talking about it.

302
00:21:54,855 --> 00:21:56,481
Hasn't Su-ryeon told you?

303
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:01,111
But they only just met.

304
00:22:01,194 --> 00:22:02,279
Hey.

305
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:07,659
You can't believe the mighty Lee Su-ryeon
is getting married, can you?

306
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:12,205
I can't either.

307
00:22:12,873 --> 00:22:15,751
I'm also worried that
they're rushing things a bit.

308
00:22:15,834 --> 00:22:17,169
It doesn't feel right.

309
00:22:17,836 --> 00:22:21,089
There also seem to be rumors
going around about the guy.

310
00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:23,842
I wish Su-ryeon would be more careful.

311
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:26,970
What kind of rumors?

312
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:31,516
They're nothing serious,

313
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:36,354
but I would've preferred a guy
who grew up in a happy family.

314
00:22:37,481 --> 00:22:39,149
I'm probably just being nosy.

315
00:22:44,696 --> 00:22:47,616
Goodness. Like I said,
I'm just being nosy.

316
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,367
As long as they like each other,
who cares?

317
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:52,329
Don't you think the two of them
are quite similar?

318
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:55,499
A couple like that may quibble,
but they live happy lives.

319
00:22:57,501 --> 00:22:59,586
Government-funded professors must resign!

320
00:22:59,669 --> 00:23:02,672
-Resign!
-Resign!

321
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:04,341
Yushin remnants must resign!

322
00:23:04,424 --> 00:23:07,511
-Resign!
-Resign!

323
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:09,012
Government-funded professors must resign!

324
00:23:09,096 --> 00:23:10,764
-Resign!
-Resign!

325
00:23:10,847 --> 00:23:12,432
-Resign!
-Resign!

326
00:23:12,516 --> 00:23:15,477
My dear student democracy activists.

327
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:21,691
We should not be onlookers or bystanders.

328
00:23:22,442 --> 00:23:27,739
We should be the leaders of the university
and the democracy movement!

329
00:23:27,823 --> 00:23:30,325
Government-funded professors must resign!

330
00:23:30,408 --> 00:23:31,743
-Resign!
-Resign!

331
00:23:31,827 --> 00:23:34,204
Government-funded professors must resign!

332
00:23:34,287 --> 00:23:36,039
-Lee Su-ryeon.
-Resign!

333
00:23:36,123 --> 00:23:37,999
Government-funded professors must resign!

334
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,252
-Lee Su-ryeon.
-Resign!

335
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:42,212
Government-funded professors must resign!

336
00:23:42,295 --> 00:23:44,714
-Hey!
-Resign!

337
00:23:53,974 --> 00:23:56,685
What's this? What are you doing here?

338
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:59,980
What else? You and I have a date.

339
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:02,065
They have a date.

340
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:06,695
We'll talk later.

341
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:08,530
I don't have time
to deal with you right now.

342
00:24:08,613 --> 00:24:11,116
Do you really have the right
to criticize government-funded professors?

343
00:24:11,199 --> 00:24:12,117
What?

344
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:16,663
You want to reap the benefits
while avoiding the responsibilities?

345
00:24:18,331 --> 00:24:21,668
Do they know that you're playing a hero

346
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:24,421
using the son of the Head
of Anti-communist Investigation?

347
00:24:25,005 --> 00:24:27,465
-What's he saying?
-I'm not sure.

348
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:32,804
Get lost while I'm still being nice.

349
00:24:39,227 --> 00:24:40,729
Gosh, seriously.

350
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:46,234
Hey, Hui-tae. What are you doing here?

351
00:24:49,779 --> 00:24:51,072
So?

352
00:24:52,073 --> 00:24:54,284
Do you want to be humiliated
in front of everyone?

353
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:07,339
Government-funded professors must resign!

354
00:25:07,422 --> 00:25:09,132
-Resign!
-Resign!

355
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:11,509
Government-funded professors must resign!

356
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:13,386
-Resign!
-Gosh!

357
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:16,514
-No.
-Gosh!

358
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:23,521
-Myeong-hee.
-Myeong-hee.

359
00:25:26,566 --> 00:25:28,526
What happened? You have a concussion?

360
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:33,240
I'm totally fine,
but this jerk still dragged me here.

361
00:25:33,323 --> 00:25:36,952
Gosh. She fell while fooling around
on the railing of the rooftop.

362
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:39,537
Hey, I only fell because you grabbed me.

363
00:25:39,621 --> 00:25:41,206
Be quiet, both of you.

364
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:45,252
So? Did you get a CT scan?

365
00:25:45,335 --> 00:25:48,296
Yes. Everything seems fine,

366
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:49,839
except for some minor symptoms
of a concussion.

367
00:25:50,799 --> 00:25:53,885
Myeong-hee,
please make sure I can leave soon.

368
00:25:53,969 --> 00:25:55,595
The protest must be
at its height right now.

369
00:25:55,679 --> 00:25:57,347
Do you still want to play a hero?

370
00:25:57,430 --> 00:26:01,309
Hey, no one will even notice
you're not there.

371
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:02,978
-What did you just say?
-Stop it.

372
00:26:03,061 --> 00:26:04,437
Stop it, you two!

373
00:26:06,314 --> 00:26:09,192
I'll go and ask if you can leave.

374
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:10,360
Wait here.

375
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:12,362
-Okay.
-You little…

376
00:26:12,445 --> 00:26:13,363
Will you…

377
00:26:15,323 --> 00:26:17,993
-Don't fight, okay?
-Okay.

378
00:26:19,995 --> 00:26:21,788
Come on. Seriously.

379
00:26:22,622 --> 00:26:24,374
Behave, okay?

380
00:26:25,041 --> 00:26:26,209
Gosh.

381
00:26:29,045 --> 00:26:31,756
-Stop it. I said, stop it.
-Let go.

382
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,174
Jeez!

383
00:26:35,510 --> 00:26:37,595
-This is so dusty.
-Did you just hit me?

384
00:26:37,679 --> 00:26:39,264
What? No, I didn't.

385
00:26:39,347 --> 00:26:42,183
Don't you think the two of them
are quite similar?

386
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,894
A couple like that may quibble,
but they live happy lives.

387
00:26:44,978 --> 00:26:47,689
-You really need to stop.
-Whatever.

388
00:26:47,772 --> 00:26:48,648
-Hey.
-What?

389
00:26:48,732 --> 00:26:49,941
-My patience has a limit.
-So?

390
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:53,486
EMERGENCY ROOM

391
00:27:00,410 --> 00:27:01,786
Myeong-hee.

392
00:27:04,289 --> 00:27:07,834
Well, I wasn't going to wait for you.

393
00:27:07,917 --> 00:27:10,837
I just had some business
at the hospital and the timing…

394
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:12,130
Where is Su-ryeon?

395
00:27:12,714 --> 00:27:14,466
I don't know. She went somewhere.

396
00:27:15,383 --> 00:27:16,968
You're hungry, aren't you?

397
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:18,970
Let's go get something to eat first.

398
00:27:19,054 --> 00:27:21,556
Then I'll sing you that song I wrote
as I promised.

399
00:27:29,272 --> 00:27:30,690
I don't want that.

400
00:27:33,651 --> 00:27:34,611
What do you mean?

401
00:27:34,694 --> 00:27:36,363
You'll tell me
we should stop seeing each other.

402
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:37,405
I don't want that.

403
00:27:41,451 --> 00:27:43,620
Did you know
that your fathers are discussing

404
00:27:44,412 --> 00:27:46,122
your marriage?

405
00:27:46,206 --> 00:27:49,334
Both you and Su-ryeon
have complicated problems to solve.

406
00:27:49,417 --> 00:27:51,461
I don't want to make things any worse
for you guys.

407
00:27:52,545 --> 00:27:53,755
Forget me and Su-ryeon.

408
00:27:54,464 --> 00:27:55,298
What about you?

409
00:27:58,551 --> 00:28:02,055
Tell me how you feel,
and I'll make everything simple.

410
00:28:08,395 --> 00:28:09,938
I'm going abroad to study.

411
00:28:10,980 --> 00:28:12,148
What?

412
00:28:12,816 --> 00:28:14,901
That's what I was trying
to tell you yesterday.

413
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:17,529
I'm leaving in a month.

414
00:28:18,571 --> 00:28:21,116
I only went on that blind date with you

415
00:28:21,699 --> 00:28:23,785
to earn my airfare.

416
00:28:30,291 --> 00:28:33,169
When will you come back?

417
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:39,592
My plan is to move there

418
00:28:40,385 --> 00:28:41,428
permanently.

419
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:45,056
So let's not do anything
we'll regret later on.

420
00:28:45,807 --> 00:28:47,517
Let's end this here.

421
00:28:48,935 --> 00:28:50,812
So we can only remember the good things.

422
00:28:56,401 --> 00:28:58,194
Wait, Myeong-hee.

423
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,621
I'm glad to have met you.

424
00:29:09,748 --> 00:29:10,957
I really mean it.

425
00:30:39,003 --> 00:30:40,463
A month?

426
00:30:41,714 --> 00:30:44,884
At this point,
even that's pretty optimistic.

427
00:30:44,968 --> 00:30:46,886
Her recovery is slow.

428
00:30:46,970 --> 00:30:49,556
I can't say for sure
how long she'll hold out.

429
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:52,016
Can't she

430
00:30:53,059 --> 00:30:54,978
still be transferred?

431
00:30:55,562 --> 00:30:57,188
That's beside the point.

432
00:30:57,272 --> 00:30:58,356
She's unconscious.

433
00:30:58,439 --> 00:31:00,483
To her, it'll make no difference
whether she's in Seoul or Gwangju.

434
00:31:00,567 --> 00:31:04,529
Don't you think it's selfish
to make her take this risk?

435
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:14,831
My gosh.

436
00:31:15,540 --> 00:31:17,458
What is it now?

437
00:31:18,334 --> 00:31:20,962
Why doesn't anything ever go my way?

438
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:30,430
Hey, be honest now.
Is everything really okay?

439
00:31:37,687 --> 00:31:39,272
Think about this.

440
00:31:40,648 --> 00:31:43,067
Let's say you just met the woman
of your dreams,

441
00:31:43,151 --> 00:31:45,653
but she's going away for good in a month.

442
00:31:45,737 --> 00:31:46,905
What would you do?

443
00:31:49,115 --> 00:31:51,826
-Is Su-ryeon going somewhere?
-I'm not talking about her!

444
00:31:53,786 --> 00:31:57,999
The woman of my dreams
who's going away for good?

445
00:32:00,001 --> 00:32:01,586
I'd give up immediately.

446
00:32:02,462 --> 00:32:03,463
Why?

447
00:32:03,546 --> 00:32:07,216
I'd rather live with regrets
than miss her for the rest of my life.

448
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:08,927
I hate heartaches.

449
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:12,263
Just continue to live the way
you always have.

450
00:32:12,347 --> 00:32:15,516
Isn't it your philosophy of life
to live lightheartedly?

451
00:32:17,685 --> 00:32:19,646
That's when it's only about my life.

452
00:32:20,688 --> 00:32:23,691
It's totally different
once another person's life is involved.

453
00:32:23,775 --> 00:32:25,234
Goodness.

454
00:32:25,818 --> 00:32:28,321
You've come a long way.

455
00:32:28,404 --> 00:32:30,156
You care about another person now?

456
00:32:30,657 --> 00:32:32,367
If you have a headache,

457
00:32:33,451 --> 00:32:35,370
why not try the solution
from our high school days?

458
00:32:35,453 --> 00:32:36,579
Here.

459
00:32:50,176 --> 00:32:52,679
Goodness. You startled me.

460
00:32:53,388 --> 00:32:56,224
-You're home late.
-Since when do you smoke?

461
00:32:57,266 --> 00:32:58,810
Well, this is…

462
00:32:59,936 --> 00:33:02,772
Go to bed early.
We have somewhere to be tomorrow.

463
00:33:02,855 --> 00:33:04,983
Dad. Your lighter.

464
00:33:06,025 --> 00:33:08,861
Keep it.
Make sure you carry it at all times.

465
00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:26,671
So, Dad is going to bring more clothes
to the camp?

466
00:33:26,754 --> 00:33:30,049
Yes, on the next market day.

467
00:33:31,384 --> 00:33:34,095
Why don't you put on
the new shoes instead?

468
00:33:34,971 --> 00:33:37,682
The shoelaces are a hassle.

469
00:33:38,349 --> 00:33:40,852
They keep getting tangled if I tie them.

470
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:47,525
You wear worn-out shoes
because shoelaces are a hassle?

471
00:33:50,319 --> 00:33:51,612
Put these on instead.

472
00:33:52,989 --> 00:33:53,948
Come on.

473
00:33:54,532 --> 00:33:57,952
I don't want to. I don't!

474
00:33:58,036 --> 00:33:59,037
Little bear.

475
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:01,664
It's all over. I messed up.

476
00:34:01,748 --> 00:34:05,710
All the kids are annoying
and I got on the wrong side of the coach.

477
00:34:14,510 --> 00:34:16,971
When something is tangled,
just untangle it.

478
00:34:17,764 --> 00:34:19,891
Untangle it carefully

479
00:34:20,516 --> 00:34:22,268
and tie it nicely again.

480
00:34:23,811 --> 00:34:27,065
If you leave it tangled, it's your loss.

481
00:34:27,815 --> 00:34:30,318
Whether it's your shoelaces or training,

482
00:34:30,985 --> 00:34:33,571
isn't running fast
the most important thing to you?

483
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:54,467
Jeong-tae, are you angry
you're not allowed to stay at the camp?

484
00:34:54,550 --> 00:34:55,843
You know how Dad is.

485
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:58,262
He barely gave permission about
you missing school to train--

486
00:34:58,346 --> 00:34:59,722
No, it's not like that.

487
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:02,100
I'll get going.

488
00:35:04,894 --> 00:35:07,271
I'll come pick you up
before Dad gets off work.

489
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:08,689
Don't come to the camp.

490
00:35:09,398 --> 00:35:11,150
Meet me here instead.

491
00:35:24,413 --> 00:35:26,916
Guys, don't run.

492
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:30,002
-Joo-bin, you're in Room One.
-Yes, coach.

493
00:35:30,086 --> 00:35:31,838
Kyung-jae, Room One.

494
00:35:33,256 --> 00:35:35,967
-Gun-woo, Room One.
-Yes, coach.

495
00:35:36,717 --> 00:35:39,053
Digestive Drink, Room Four. Work hard.

496
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:40,138
Yes, coach.

497
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:43,182
-Attention.
-Attention!

498
00:35:43,266 --> 00:35:45,017
I can't hear you. Attention!

499
00:35:45,101 --> 00:35:45,935
-Attention!
-Attention!

500
00:35:46,018 --> 00:35:48,312
You have just three minutes.

501
00:35:48,396 --> 00:35:50,356
Go to your rooms and unpack.

502
00:35:50,439 --> 00:35:52,984
Change into training clothes
and get back here.

503
00:35:53,067 --> 00:35:54,235
Ready.

504
00:36:00,074 --> 00:36:02,994
Too slow. Hurry up!

505
00:36:03,077 --> 00:36:04,328
-Yes, coach!
-Yes, coach!

506
00:36:18,134 --> 00:36:19,886
Jeong-tae, are you in Room Four too?

507
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:23,264
It's just my luck.

508
00:36:24,473 --> 00:36:25,808
Move.

509
00:36:28,227 --> 00:36:29,896
You have one minute left!

510
00:36:29,979 --> 00:36:32,315
There will be a penalty
for the one who comes last.

511
00:36:39,864 --> 00:36:41,282
Guys, hurry.

512
00:36:45,244 --> 00:36:46,704
Hey, Digestive Drink!

513
00:36:46,787 --> 00:36:48,581
What?

514
00:36:48,664 --> 00:36:50,082
