Auntie, don't call him like that.

572
00:39:46,842 --> 00:39:48,844
I'll make coffee.

573
00:39:48,928 --> 00:39:50,179
Take a seat.

574
00:39:51,806 --> 00:39:53,015
Yes, take a seat.

575
00:39:53,099 --> 00:39:55,601
Enjoy the food, everyone.

576
00:39:56,811 --> 00:39:59,897
Yes, thank you for coming.

577
00:39:59,980 --> 00:40:02,525
CHANGHWA PHARMACEUTICALS AERIAL VIEW

578
00:40:05,236 --> 00:40:08,489
You'll buy patented medicines
from other countries and manufacture them?

579
00:40:09,073 --> 00:40:11,492
Will this be more profitable
than just importing them?

580
00:40:12,326 --> 00:40:13,786
Yes, of course.

581
00:40:15,496 --> 00:40:17,248
Being able to supply
such medicines on our own

582
00:40:17,331 --> 00:40:20,960
without having to rely on importing them
will help strengthen our country.

583
00:40:22,962 --> 00:40:24,755
You have such an admirable son.

584
00:40:25,297 --> 00:40:28,551
Gosh, he has grand plans
but has a long way to go.

585
00:40:30,261 --> 00:40:32,721
We underestimated
building a pharmaceutical factory.

586
00:40:32,805 --> 00:40:35,141
It costs a fortune.

587
00:40:37,476 --> 00:40:40,479
One of my in-laws is looking for
a company to invest in.

588
00:40:41,355 --> 00:40:43,023
Shall I introduce you to him?

589
00:40:43,107 --> 00:40:44,233
Pardon me?

590
00:40:44,316 --> 00:40:47,278
We'd be grateful, but you don't have to.

591
00:40:47,361 --> 00:40:49,864
This isn't some stranger's business.
We're a family now.

592
00:40:52,408 --> 00:40:54,994
You're the brother
of my future daughter-in-law.

593
00:41:02,543 --> 00:41:04,462
Make two cups of coffee for me.

594
00:41:04,545 --> 00:41:06,422
-No sugar, please.
-Sure.

595
00:41:07,089 --> 00:41:08,132
Hey.

596
00:41:08,924 --> 00:41:11,677
Is that the guy?
Su-chan's future brother-in-law.

597
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:13,053
The one born out of wedlock.

598
00:41:14,972 --> 00:41:18,225
He wasn't just born out of wedlock.
His mother was a courtesan.

599
00:41:19,018 --> 00:41:21,770
My gosh, what is
Su-chan's family thinking?

600
00:41:21,854 --> 00:41:23,898
I understand their daughter
is a troublemaker,

601
00:41:23,981 --> 00:41:26,275
but how could they marry her off
to someone's illegitimate son?

602
00:41:26,358 --> 00:41:28,486
Come on. I heard he's a med student.

603
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:29,987
And he's good-looking.

604
00:41:30,070 --> 00:41:33,324
He'd better be.
His mother was a courtesan after all.

605
00:41:33,407 --> 00:41:35,576
Keep it down. He'll hear you.

606
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:40,080
I was born out of wedlock.

607
00:41:42,291 --> 00:41:44,001
But what's the problem with that?

608
00:41:44,084 --> 00:41:47,796
Thanks to our pasts, we turned out
to be strong and interesting people.

609
00:41:54,011 --> 00:41:55,471
My goodness.

610
00:41:55,554 --> 00:41:59,016
If you let this year go by,
it'll be too late.

611
00:41:59,099 --> 00:42:00,893
There's a right time for everything.

612
00:42:01,477 --> 00:42:02,811
You won't be
an eligible bachelorette forever.

613
00:42:02,895 --> 00:42:04,188
Why would you put it off?

614
00:42:04,271 --> 00:42:07,024
-Here's your coffee.
-Thank you.

615
00:42:07,107 --> 00:42:09,860
-Stop it.
-Miss, are you a bookkeeper?

616
00:42:10,569 --> 00:42:12,029
No, I'm Su-ryeon's friend.

617
00:42:12,696 --> 00:42:15,074
My gosh.
You kept making coffee over there,

618
00:42:15,157 --> 00:42:17,535
so I thought you worked at a coffee shop.

619
00:42:17,618 --> 00:42:20,204
Don't get me wrong.
It's because you're pretty.

620
00:42:20,287 --> 00:42:22,540
-Did you go to college together?
-Listen to me.

621
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:23,916
Do you have a boyfriend?

622
00:42:26,418 --> 00:42:27,628
She's my guest.

623
00:42:31,882 --> 00:42:33,008
Really?

624
00:42:34,218 --> 00:42:36,845
Myeong-hee, let's go. I'll take you home.

625
00:42:37,721 --> 00:42:38,764
Come on.

626
00:42:47,106 --> 00:42:48,440
Enjoy the coffee.

627
00:42:51,986 --> 00:42:53,028
I'm off.

628
00:42:57,700 --> 00:42:59,410
We should get going too, ma'am.

629
00:42:59,493 --> 00:43:01,203
-Shall we?
-Okay.

630
00:43:01,287 --> 00:43:03,247
-See you.
-Okay, see you.

631
00:43:17,303 --> 00:43:20,139
You should never force yourself to do
what you're not used to.

632
00:43:21,599 --> 00:43:24,184
If I keep forcing myself like this,
I may actually fall ill.

633
00:43:24,268 --> 00:43:25,644
Let's end this here.

634
00:43:26,228 --> 00:43:27,271
What?

635
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:31,358
-Hey, you're also--
-I'll give you three days.

636
00:43:31,442 --> 00:43:33,819
Whether you tell the truth or another lie,

637
00:43:33,902 --> 00:43:36,030
do what it takes to deal with your family.

638
00:43:36,113 --> 00:43:37,948
If we take this further,
we can't get out of it.

639
00:43:40,159 --> 00:43:41,952
What if I say no?

640
00:43:44,204 --> 00:43:45,831
Then I'll do whatever I want.

641
00:43:59,053 --> 00:44:00,471
What? Med school?

642
00:44:01,055 --> 00:44:03,932
Myeong-hee, I'm so impressed.

643
00:44:04,016 --> 00:44:05,851
It's nothing impressive.

644
00:44:05,934 --> 00:44:09,063
The med schools here only admit those
who will become doctors,

645
00:44:09,146 --> 00:44:12,566
whereas everyone gets admitted in Germany,
but few survive.

646
00:44:13,275 --> 00:44:15,152
I have to do a good job
once I start school.

647
00:44:15,235 --> 00:44:17,154
People who are overly modest
can be annoying, you see.

648
00:44:20,366 --> 00:44:22,034
So when do you leave?

649
00:44:22,910 --> 00:44:24,828
In a month. That's the plan now.

650
00:44:25,496 --> 00:44:27,748
What? In a month?

651
00:44:28,749 --> 00:44:32,252
It all depends on the situation,
so it might change,

652
00:44:33,462 --> 00:44:35,130
but that's the plan for now.

653
00:44:35,214 --> 00:44:37,299
That's too soon…

654
00:44:37,383 --> 00:44:40,094
I mean, that's soon.

655
00:44:40,886 --> 00:44:42,638
A month will fly by.

656
