Hold him down.

662
00:45:30,352 --> 00:45:31,520
You idiots.

663
00:45:33,188 --> 00:45:35,274
I told you to interrogate him,
not butcher him.

664
00:45:35,941 --> 00:45:38,193
Who will take responsibility
if things go south in this day and age?

665
00:45:38,277 --> 00:45:39,486
We're sorry, sir.

666
00:45:40,988 --> 00:45:43,824
Sir, please spare me.

667
00:45:43,907 --> 00:45:45,242
Don't kill me!

668
00:45:46,785 --> 00:45:48,245
Sit up!

669
00:45:49,163 --> 00:45:52,499
Please, sir…
I really didn't do anything wrong.

670
00:45:53,584 --> 00:45:55,002
-Please--
-Hey.

671
00:45:59,590 --> 00:46:01,967
I really didn't do anything wrong!

672
00:46:02,050 --> 00:46:04,470
I did nothing wrong!

673
00:46:05,387 --> 00:46:06,555
Dad.

674
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:11,852
Please believe me! I didn't…

675
00:46:11,935 --> 00:46:14,354
-I'm sorry, sir. We'll quickly…
-Forget it.

676
00:46:15,063 --> 00:46:16,523
Have someone tail him.

677
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:19,818
The student council executive?
We're already on it.

678
00:46:19,902 --> 00:46:20,861
No.

679
00:46:21,987 --> 00:46:23,238
My son.

680
00:46:25,949 --> 00:46:29,286
GWANGJU PEACE HOSPITAL
EMERGENCY ROOM

681
00:46:30,913 --> 00:46:33,081
My goodness, I'm in the main sector again.

682
00:46:35,918 --> 00:46:37,836
It's already May.

683
00:46:38,462 --> 00:46:40,005
Time really flies.

684
00:47:09,326 --> 00:47:10,869
I'LL PASS THE EXAM THIS YEAR
NO MATTER WHAT!

685
00:47:15,332 --> 00:47:16,750
Oh, right.

686
00:47:16,833 --> 00:47:21,171
Darn, a year has passed already
but I can still smell my brother's stink.

687
00:47:22,256 --> 00:47:23,423
Dad!

688
00:47:25,008 --> 00:47:26,552
-Dad!
-What?

689
00:47:26,635 --> 00:47:29,263
-Dad.
-What is it? I'm busy.

690
00:47:29,346 --> 00:47:33,183
Can you give me some of those mothballs?
I need to get rid of that horrible stink.

691
00:47:33,267 --> 00:47:35,644
I already put mothballs in that room
a long time ago.

692
00:47:35,727 --> 00:47:37,187
-Seriously.
-Come on.

693
00:47:37,271 --> 00:47:39,815
-I'm so busy. Goodness.
-Come on. Hurry.

694
00:47:44,945 --> 00:47:46,530
Yes?

695
00:47:47,656 --> 00:47:50,242
Yes, who is it?

696
00:47:59,668 --> 00:48:00,877
Hui-tae?

697
00:48:01,837 --> 00:48:03,380
How did you find where I live?

698
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:05,799
I mean, why are you here?

699
00:48:05,882 --> 00:48:07,759
Myeong-hee. I…

700
00:48:08,802 --> 00:48:10,804
Excuse me. Where is…

701
00:48:11,722 --> 00:48:13,807
Are you crazy?
What do you think you're doing?

702
00:48:13,890 --> 00:48:15,475
There are people in there.

703
00:48:15,559 --> 00:48:18,770
I'm glad. I wanted to say hi to them.

704
00:48:18,854 --> 00:48:20,564
Wait, Hui-tae.

705
00:48:20,647 --> 00:48:22,816
Do you not remember what I said?

706
00:48:22,899 --> 00:48:23,942
How can you…

707
00:48:24,776 --> 00:48:27,154
Gosh, can you let go of me?

708
00:48:27,237 --> 00:48:28,822
-Is he already here?
-Come on.

709
00:48:28,905 --> 00:48:30,616
Hello.

710
00:48:39,249 --> 00:48:40,125
No!

711
00:48:46,173 --> 00:48:47,132
Hui-tae!

712
00:48:48,675 --> 00:48:49,926
Mr. Hwang!

713
00:48:50,552 --> 00:48:51,511
Gosh.

714
00:49:03,148 --> 00:49:06,443
Have you lost your mind?
What did you do to our tutor?

715
00:49:07,194 --> 00:49:09,696
What? Tutor?

716
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:13,367
Hui-tae is going to be my tutor
starting today.

717
00:49:13,450 --> 00:49:15,702
Don't worry about it.

718
00:49:17,829 --> 00:49:20,415
Wow, the taste is perfect.

719
00:49:49,236 --> 00:49:50,362
Wait.

720
00:49:53,031 --> 00:49:55,701
This belongs to my brother,
but it's all out of tune.

721
00:49:56,368 --> 00:49:58,495
Do you want to tune it for me?

722
00:50:00,747 --> 00:50:01,873
Later.

723
00:50:02,791 --> 00:50:04,126
There we go.

724
00:50:07,003 --> 00:50:11,508
First of all, let's take a look at this.

725
00:50:11,591 --> 00:50:12,968
REPORT CARD, LEE JIN-A

726
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:15,429
Let's see.

727
00:50:16,513 --> 00:50:19,349
Ethics, D, History, C,

728
00:50:19,433 --> 00:50:20,559
Math, F.

729
00:50:22,561 --> 00:50:24,146
Jin-a, what is your dream?

730
00:50:24,229 --> 00:50:25,272
What?

731
00:50:26,148 --> 00:50:28,066
My dream is to become a radio producer.

732
00:50:28,150 --> 00:50:30,318
I want to produce a music show
like Forgotten Nights.

733
00:50:30,402 --> 00:50:32,154
I see.

734
00:50:33,822 --> 00:50:36,867
But Jin-a, you know what?

735
00:50:40,036 --> 00:50:43,039
Do I have to be good at math
to be a producer?

736
00:50:44,791 --> 00:50:46,376
No.

737
00:50:46,460 --> 00:50:50,088
You're already destined
to be good at math.

738
00:50:51,465 --> 00:50:53,341
-I am?
-Yes.

739
00:50:53,425 --> 00:50:54,384
Listen.

740
00:50:54,468 --> 00:50:58,013
Pythagoras, who is known for his theorem,
was the first to create a scale.

741
00:50:58,096 --> 00:50:59,598
And the father of music, Bach,

742
00:50:59,681 --> 00:51:02,058
composed songs
based on mathematical calculations.

743
00:51:02,809 --> 00:51:03,894
Do you know what that means?

744
00:51:05,395 --> 00:51:08,273
It means that math is music.

745
00:51:08,356 --> 00:51:09,858
And music is math.

746
00:51:09,941 --> 00:51:12,194
But the thing is, you are a music fanatic.

747
00:51:12,277 --> 00:51:15,447
You've unknowingly mastered
the nature of numbers already,

748
00:51:15,530 --> 00:51:17,991
and you're destined to be good at math.

749
00:51:18,658 --> 00:51:19,868
Like me.

750
00:51:20,660 --> 00:51:21,787
So?

751
00:51:22,370 --> 00:51:24,247
Are you prepared to accept your destiny?

752
00:51:24,831 --> 00:51:26,249
-Yes.
-Good.

753
00:51:26,833 --> 00:51:28,960
-Get in there already.
-Why should I…

754
00:51:31,129 --> 00:51:32,756
Go give Mr. Hwang some apples.

755
00:51:42,682 --> 00:51:45,352
What is this?

756
00:51:45,435 --> 00:51:46,436
An apple?

757
00:51:49,105 --> 00:51:51,107
I was mistaken earlier.

758
00:51:53,485 --> 00:51:55,862
Why didn't you tell me you were her tutor?

759
00:51:56,446 --> 00:51:58,156
Is this really an apple?

760
00:52:01,701 --> 00:52:03,245
I'm sorry.

761
00:52:04,204 --> 00:52:06,832
I've washed your shirt, so don't worry.

762
00:52:07,499 --> 00:52:09,501
It really is an apple.

763
00:52:13,129 --> 00:52:14,256
Yes?

764
00:52:15,423 --> 00:52:16,633
I'm sorry to interrupt.

765
00:52:16,716 --> 00:52:19,594
Mr. Hwang, can you stay for dinner
after today's lesson?

766
00:52:21,137 --> 00:52:22,639
Dinner?

767
00:52:24,432 --> 00:52:25,934
I'd be happy to.

768
00:52:27,853 --> 00:52:28,895
Here we go.

769
00:52:31,481 --> 00:52:34,317
Do you drink?

770
00:52:34,401 --> 00:52:37,863
I was waiting to open this
when my son gets discharged from the army.

771
00:52:37,946 --> 00:52:39,364
Wait.

772
00:52:39,948 --> 00:52:40,782
Gosh,

773
00:52:41,449 --> 00:52:44,202
then you shouldn't open
such a precious thing.

774
00:52:44,286 --> 00:52:47,163
-I'll go out and get some makgeolli.
-No need.

775
00:52:47,247 --> 00:52:48,790
Oh, come on.

776
00:52:48,874 --> 00:52:52,335
It's all right. You're like my son.

777
00:52:56,339 --> 00:52:59,801
In that case,
I'll have just one glass, sir.

778
00:53:02,721 --> 00:53:04,514
Do you even know what that's made of?

779
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:07,767
This is really…

780
00:53:09,436 --> 00:53:12,147
Medicine. It's medicine.

781
00:53:12,230 --> 00:53:13,857
-Mr. Hwang.
-Yes, sir.

782
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:16,109
Thank you.

783
00:53:18,028 --> 00:53:19,863
Let's clink glasses.

784
00:53:21,156 --> 00:53:22,240
Cheers.

785
00:53:33,793 --> 00:53:37,505
Do you know what I did for my wife?

786
00:53:38,089 --> 00:53:42,510
I left my home
and started living with my in-laws.

787
00:53:44,971 --> 00:53:46,431
Can you stop talking about that?

788
00:53:46,514 --> 00:53:49,017
This is the third time already.

789
00:53:49,100 --> 00:53:53,188
This story doesn't get old
even if I tell it ten times.

790
00:53:53,271 --> 00:53:55,774
You can't listen to it
without shedding tears.

791
00:53:55,857 --> 00:53:58,401
Get your handkerchief ready.

792
00:54:00,946 --> 00:54:05,575
You know, I used to be quite popular
in my old neighborhood.

793
00:54:06,368 --> 00:54:08,370
But you know what? After…

794
00:54:08,453 --> 00:54:10,956
-Hui-tae, you should go now.
-I came here…

795
00:54:11,039 --> 00:54:13,708
If he gets more drunk,
you'll never get out of here.

796
00:54:13,792 --> 00:54:16,878
-It's okay.
-Stop being stubborn.

797
00:54:16,962 --> 00:54:18,088
I'll be fine.

798
00:54:18,171 --> 00:54:19,714
Myeong-hee.

799
00:54:19,798 --> 00:54:21,299
Can't you see I'm having a talk
with my son?

800
00:54:21,383 --> 00:54:24,844
What are you whispering to my new son?

801
00:54:25,428 --> 00:54:26,805
He should get going now.

802
00:54:26,888 --> 00:54:29,724
It's almost time for the curfew.

803
00:54:30,308 --> 00:54:31,393
Curfew?

804
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:39,484
You can spend the night here.

805
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:42,153
-What?
-We'll spread out a blanket

806
00:54:42,237 --> 00:54:46,074
-in the living room and sprawl out!
-But…

807
00:54:46,157 --> 00:54:47,993
-I'd love that.
-Really?

808
00:54:48,076 --> 00:54:51,037
My shirt isn't dry yet anyway.

809
00:54:51,121 --> 00:54:53,373
-It isn't dry yet!
-Right!

810
00:54:53,456 --> 00:54:55,834
It isn't dry yet!

811
00:54:57,127 --> 00:54:58,753
-Son!
-Dad!

812
00:54:58,837 --> 00:55:01,506
-Let's have another drink.
-Give me another glass.

813
00:55:01,589 --> 00:55:04,801
Sure thing. Here you go.

814
00:56:46,277 --> 00:56:47,904
Are you drunk?

815
00:56:47,987 --> 00:56:49,531
Why are you
playing the guitar at this hour?

816
00:56:50,782 --> 00:56:51,950
I'm not drunk.

817
00:56:53,535 --> 00:56:55,578
I'm just parched

818
00:56:55,662 --> 00:56:57,997
from all that soy sauce earlier.
That's all.

819
00:57:00,208 --> 00:57:03,378
Well, then… Should I get you
some honey tea or something?

820
00:57:04,170 --> 00:57:05,296
Don't bother.

821
00:57:06,714 --> 00:57:08,258
Suit yourself then.

822
00:57:08,341 --> 00:57:09,968
I don't need any honey tea, but…

823
00:57:19,644 --> 00:57:21,938
Can you sit with me for a moment?

824
00:57:53,219 --> 00:57:54,304
I'm sorry.

825
00:57:57,098 --> 00:57:58,141
For what?

826
00:58:04,147 --> 00:58:05,648
I feel like I'm being selfish

827
00:58:06,399 --> 00:58:09,027
and causing you trouble again and again.

828
00:58:13,281 --> 00:58:16,451
You didn't cause too much trouble.

829
00:58:24,250 --> 00:58:25,710
After what you told me,

830
00:58:27,295 --> 00:58:30,715
I thought hard about the remaining month.

831
00:58:33,843 --> 00:58:35,428
And I realized,

832
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:37,597
it's not the month we have
that I'm afraid of,

833
00:58:38,223 --> 00:58:41,059
but how much I'll be hurt
after that month is gone.

834
00:58:44,395 --> 00:58:46,272
I like you, Myeong-hee,

835
00:58:46,940 --> 00:58:49,442
and I'll only continue
to like you more and more.

836
00:58:52,403 --> 00:58:55,031
Goodness, you and your cheesy words.

837
00:59:11,881 --> 00:59:15,510
I look forward to May every year.

838
00:59:17,178 --> 00:59:20,098
On a May night, even if you sing badly,

839
00:59:21,349 --> 00:59:22,934
the grasshoppers help you out.

840
00:59:23,768 --> 00:59:25,144
The grasshoppers?

841
00:59:26,062 --> 00:59:27,146
Yes.

842
00:59:31,526 --> 00:59:33,194
Let's see here.

843
01:01:23,262 --> 01:01:24,931
Whenever I think of you, Myeong-hee,

844
01:01:26,015 --> 01:01:27,809
I can't help but sing.

845
01:01:32,730 --> 01:01:33,731
Goodness.

846
01:01:34,565 --> 01:01:36,526
There you go again
with those cheesy words.

847
01:01:46,411 --> 01:01:47,537
Myeong-hee.

848
01:01:50,832 --> 01:01:54,502
Do you want to go out with me
just until the end of May?

849
01:02:39,130 --> 01:02:42,425
-What's your relationship with Ms. Jang?
-I'd say, we're offender and victim.

850
01:02:42,508 --> 01:02:44,177
Come out while I'm being nice.

851
01:02:44,260 --> 01:02:45,094
Get out of here!

852
01:02:45,178 --> 01:02:47,305
-Are you free tomorrow?
-I have somewhere to be.

853
01:02:47,388 --> 01:02:49,223
-I'll come with you.
-You don't even know where.

854
01:02:49,307 --> 01:02:51,142
-It doesn't matter.
-Keep a good eye on your daughter.

855
01:02:51,225 --> 01:02:53,686
She's not a kid anymore.
I won't go easy now.

856
01:02:53,770 --> 01:02:55,188
Have you been spying on me?

857
01:02:55,271 --> 01:02:58,107
Well, let's just say I'm interested
in my future daughter-in-law.

858
01:02:58,191 --> 01:03:01,444
-I have no interest in getting married.
-That family will help our business.

859
01:03:01,527 --> 01:03:03,571
My father's factory
will be built in a month.

860
01:03:03,654 --> 01:03:05,198
Let's keep this up until then.

861
01:03:05,281 --> 01:03:08,242
We shouldn't cross the line
just to save ourselves for now.

